"{\"uid\": \"surfacemag.com-articles-grand-palais-restoration-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Paris has embarked on a dizzying array of ambitious projects in the interest of putting its best foot forward when the 2024 Summer Olympic Games kick off in about two months.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 174, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 5, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.468843489543525e-20, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is making the Seine swimmable-a dubious proposition by any stretch, yet one thatLos Angeles 2028is taking a cue from-along with15-minute cities, a \\\"green\\\" Olympic Village, and Mathieu Lehanneur's transformation of Mus\\u00e9e d'Orsay's clocktower into a romanticAirbnb.\", \"from\": 175, \"to\": 444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 195, \"end\": 200, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2791435942356243e-20, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 336, \"end\": 351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.6910134256517833e-16, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 395, \"end\": 408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mus\\u00e9e_d'Orsay\", \"score\": 0.9999999943702278, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mus\\u00e9e d'Orsay\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mus\\u00e9e_d'Orsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mus\\u00e9e_d'Orsay\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While these projects and more (like those outrageousanti-sex beds) have consumed the lion's share of press around civic undertakings,Chatillon Architecteshas embarked on an all-consuming restoration of theGrandPalais.\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At present, two shifts of around 900 workers are refurbishing the Beaux-Arts landmark to get its central nave in shape to host taekwondo and fencing.\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 812, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Originally built in three years by a crew of just 1,500 and overseen by four architects for the1900 World's Fair, the scale and scope of the refurbishment now in the hands of Fran\\u00e7ois Chatillon is staggering.\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 1022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a recent interview with theFinancial Times, the architect shared that he's working with no fewer than 50 companies and 200 subcontractors.\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1164, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a result, even a seemingly simple task like choosing a shade of concrete for the nave's floor took three months.\", \"from\": 1165, \"to\": 1280, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The project's full scope includes unifying its galleries and naves, rehabilitating its balconies and cantilevered concrete walkway, replacing walls and partitions added over the years with transparent glass panes, and restoring period details like the bronze adornments on the main nave'sgrandstaircase.\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1584, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's little wonder that the project has been in the works since 2021.\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even before it shuttered, theGrandPalaishad cultivated a reputation for captivating gutsy, outside-the-box thinkers.Anish KapoorandKarl Lagerfeldpushed the 188,000-square-foot dome's spatial boundaries with Kapoor'sLeviathansculpture and Lagerfeld's larger-than-life rocket for Chanel's Fall/Winter 2017 runway show).\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1934, \"end\": 1940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chanel\", \"score\": 0.9999359752765814, \"rank\": 6.402882282232428e-05, \"text\": \"Chanel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chanel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chanel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Upon its full completion in 2025, the fully restoredPalaiswill welcome 60,000 plants in a sprawling landscape inspired by the neighboring Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es gardens, and two of its galleries will host the collections of the Centre Pompidou while it undergoesrefurbishment.\", \"from\": 1974, \"to\": 2242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2112, \"end\": 2126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"score\": 0.9938637728104254, \"rank\": 0.005341849563968814, \"text\": \"Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The opportunity to redevelop an icon is amazing, but theGrandPalaisfeels like so much more,\\\" Chatillon says.\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2353, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's the opportunity to return a permanent public use to the building, to redevelop the surrounding grounds, to connect the building back with the city, and to adapt it for the Olympics and future generations.\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2564, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is truly a once-in-a-lifetime project.\\\"\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2609, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Next Article  Plus, new research on invasive rats' role in deforesting Easter Island, and Sarah Hoover memoir...  Festive season is upon us, and Worthlessstudios sure has plenty to celebrate.\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2802, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2701, \"end\": 2706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Jane_Smith\", \"score\": 0.999432470652784,